      "explanation": "Correct: D — Correct. The 14 Common European Data Spaces cover Agriculture, Cultural heritage, Energy, Finance, Green Deal, Health (EHDS — first operational), Industry & manufacturing, Language, Media, Mobility, Public administration, Research & innovation, Skills, and Tourism. Each pools sector-specific data under common governance, technical building blocks (Simpl) and support (DSSC — Data Spaces Support Centre).\n· A: Only some data spaces are accompanied by binding regulations (EHDS for health). Others progress through pilots, implementing acts and sector-specific initiatives — so no uniform effective date exists.\n· B: Data spaces are technology-neutral. Some pilots use blockchain; most do not.\n· C: Not a single service — they are networks of participants using shared standards and governance, not a monolithic centrally operated cloud with shared IT infrastructure per sector domain.",
