      "explanation": "Correct: A — Correct. Metadata is descriptive, structural, administrative or provenance information about a data asset — title, author, creation date, schema, lineage, access rules, quality indicators. Good metadata makes data findable, understandable and trustworthy, which is why it anchors FAIR and modern data-catalogue practice.\n· B: Encryption is a confidentiality control applied at rest in the storage backend, not a definition of metadata.\n· C: Retention age is a lifecycle concept; old data isn't metadata merely because it's old.\n· D: Model metadata is one kind of metadata, but the concept is much broader — not exclusively ML artefacts.",
