      "correct": "A",
      "explanation": "Correct: A — Correct. Data lineage answers 'where did this number come from?' by tracing data through sources, pipelines, transformations and consuming reports. It is essential for impact analysis (what breaks if this table changes?), regulatory accountability and root-cause analysis. Modern catalogues auto-ingest lineage from dbt, Airflow, Spark and warehouse query logs.\n· B: Hardware origin is an infrastructure supply-chain fact, not data lineage.\n· C: Login history is an access log, not a transformation trail on the data itself.\n· D: Model training runs are MLOps metadata — lineage is broader, covering any data transformation.",
