      "explanation": "Correct: B — Correct. Completeness has two common dimensions: (1) record-level — all required attributes filled (no unexpected NULLs where values must exist), (2) dataset-level — expected volume received (no partial batches, no missing delta). It is one of the five inherent ISO/IEC 25012 characteristics and a frequent failure mode in pipelines.\n· A: Encryption is a security property, not a completeness check. They are orthogonal concerns, regardless of how many hops the feed takes.\n· C: Logical consistency is a consistency check, not a completeness check. Different DQ dimension.\n· D: Access to records for departments is a governance / access control concern, not a completeness check.",
