      "correct": "D",
      "explanation": "Correct: D — Correct. Art. 32(1) lists examples of appropriate measures: pseudonymisation and encryption; ensuring ongoing confidentiality, integrity, availability and resilience; ability to restore availability and access in a timely manner after an incident; and a process for regularly testing, assessing and evaluating the effectiveness of the measures. Note the CIA triad sitting underneath.\n· A: Password length is not mentioned as an Art. 32 example — and no single sole measure covers the whole risk-appropriate universe for controllers and processors.\n· B: Blockchain is not listed or mandated by Art. 32. The article is technology-neutral.\n· C: Publishing logs openly would itself be a security risk. Transparency rules are elsewhere (privacy notices).",
