        "B": "Admin-by-default across the organisation on every single system is the opposite of least privilege — maximum privilege.",
        "C": "Time-boxed access can support least privilege but a fixed 24-hour auto-revocation isn't the definition.",
        "D": "Alphabetical ordering isn't a security principle at all."
