      "explanation": "Correct: C — Correct. Data fabric (Gartner) is a metadata-driven integration architecture that weaves distributed data assets into a coherent whole. Its defining traits: active metadata collection and analysis; a knowledge graph linking assets; AI / ML assisting with data discovery, matching, lineage and quality; unified semantic layer; and policy-driven access across on-prem, cloud and edge. Unlike data mesh (which is primarily an organisational / domain-driven approach), data fabric is primarily a technical / metadata-first approach. The two can coexist.\n· A: Data fabric is a logical architecture, not a physical cabling standard — despite the 'fabric' wording.\n· B: Fabric and mesh overlap but are not synonyms. Fabric emphasises integration via metadata / AI; mesh emphasises domain-oriented ownership.\n· D: Container orchestration is Kubernetes / Nomad territory — unrelated to the data-fabric concept.",
